Chess.com has a mode where it calls out a square grid and you have to click on that one on the board. That helped me alot. Another way that helped me was I would play tic tac toe with my friends but with no pen or paper we would only call out coordinance. Example the top left would be A3 and the bottom right would be C1. After a while we would expand the board and start to put chess pieces then do tactics on a 5 by 5 grid then a 6 by 6 and so on and so forth until we got to 8 by 8.

Isn't it crazy?? I have a similar experience. I used to think it was all normal and then when I found out it wasn't everything just fell apart for me. I started to question everything I did since I noticed I was carrying on traits from my abusive household. This caused me to go into depression and hate everything and cut of friends and family. It's just crazy how little control people have of their childhood.
